item.title: a song of near creatures
item.media:title: a song of near creatures
item.media:description:
happy birthday to the radiant LadyBitterblue, one of my oldest and most treasured friends here. this poem has been FAR too many of your birthdays in the making but i finally (!!!!) finished it enough in time for this year (although i'll probably come back and keep whittling with it :~D!) i'm sending you so, so much love and magic today and always, lowenzahn. here's to you and all the light you bring. ♥♥♥♥♥

(ps i just realized this is my 400th poem?????????? WOW WHO KNEW!!!! idk if it's as huge of a milestone as i feel like it is but thank you to everyone who's supported my poetry over all these years. im so so grateful for your support and encouragement ily all!!!!!)
item.media:text:
so may you be brambled
with your woodland wonder:
your heart like a berry
your stories its seeds
dazzling dappled in the
thicket of it all.

yes, this is about
every fleck of you
fawned, in the dearness
of dawn. and you're dancing
your soft step stitches
into daybreak, so it knows

when the night cracks open
and the sun slips through
there's a hopeful kind of (w)hole
and a lustered line of healing
in its lifetime, ripe with love.

darling, when the fall fades in
with all its feeling
you still follow: & in
the half light of the hollow
you make meadows
out of me.

happy birthday to the radiant LadyBitterblue, one of my oldest and most treasured friends here. this poem has been FAR too many of your birthdays in the making but i finally (!!!!) finished it enough in time for this year (although i'll probably come back and keep whittling with it :~D!) i'm sending you so, so much love and magic today and always, lowenzahn. here's to you and all the light you bring. ♥♥♥♥♥

(ps i just realized this is my 400th poem?????????? WOW WHO KNEW!!!! idk if it's as huge of a milestone as i feel like it is but thank you to everyone who's supported my poetry over all these years. im so so grateful for your support and encouragement ily all!!!!!)

item.title: Gilded Dragon Hide Purse (multiple views)
item.media:title: Gilded Dragon Hide Purse (multiple views)
item.media:description:
Back in November I decided to make this "dragon hide" purse for myself as well as a simple black purse commission for a client as part of the DayKnight community's 30 day project challenge. While the commissioned purse went without a hitch, I experienced many technical issues during the construction of this purse. Anywho now that I've finally finished both and updated the project website, it's sharing time!

Both purses feature 3 pockets (1 zipped, and 2 open) inside along the interior lining. The exterior fabrics of both purses are also reinforced with vinyl for added strength and longevity. The vinyl that I used to reinforce the red scale pattern fabric on this purse was a bit floppier than expected, so I also glued some cardboard along the central panel inside the purse for added structure.

Other photos related to this project:
www.deviantart.com/bluejay2/ar…
www.deviantart.com/bluejay2/ar…
www.deviantart.com/bluejay2/ar…
www.deviantart.com/bluejay2/ar…

For more info and photos, feel free to check out my progress on both purses at the project website here: dk30.day9.tv/projects/43123640…

And as always, feel free to check out my professional Facebook page here: www.facebook.com/jennyoungart/
Visitors are always welcome!

item.title: Winter's Procession
item.media:title: Winter's Procession
item.media:description:
A young girl on pony-back stumbles upon a strange forest ritual. The trees themselves have come alive to wind solemnly through the wintry woodland. Her pony's bell sends out a nervous ring as they pause to regard her.
